page.title: 09HUMBIE SCHOOL COMMUNITY
page.content: MANY PEOPLE VISIT OUR SCHOOL AND ARE EMPLOYED HERE.OUR LUNCHES COME BY VAN FROM A BIGGER SCHOOL SIX MILES AWAY. THE FOOD IS IN TINS.OUR DINNER LADY SETS THE TABLES AND SERVES THE MEAL.WE USUALLY HAVE CHIPS OR POTATOES,A VEGETABLE AND MEAT OR FISH.MACARONI AND PIZZA ARE FAVOURITES HERE. OUR SEWING TEACHER COMES ON MONDAYS. WE MAKE ALL SORTS OF THINGS AND DO COOKING TOO.ON THURSDAY WE HAVE GYM. WE DO GYMNASTICS OR GAMES OR DANCE. WE HAVE BEEN ORIENTEERING,SWIMMING AND HAD TENNIS LESSONS ON A COURT IN THE GARDEN OF A BIG HOUSE IN THE VILLAGE. OUR LADY JANITOR KEEPS THE SCHOOL CLEAN AND LOOKS AFTER THE BOILER.OUR TEACHER ALSO HAS A SECRETARY AND A RELIEF TEACHER TO HELP HER EACH WEEK. OUR SCHOOL IS A VERY BUSY PLACE.
